1
00:00:17,236 --> 00:00:20,666
(Chicago Typewriter)

2
00:05:00,063 --> 00:05:01,163
Don't be so ridiculous.

3
00:05:01,623 --> 00:05:04,063
No idiot would let a novel ruin his life.

4
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:07,823
You're the one who ruined your life.

5
00:06:27,223 --> 00:06:30,123
What are you waiting for? Go ahead and call the police.

6
00:06:35,193 --> 00:06:37,523
(Chicago Typewriter)

7
00:06:37,523 --> 00:06:39,293
- What's going on? - What happened?

8
00:06:38,994 --> 00:06:40,438
[<i>Episode 2</i>]

9
00:06:39,563 --> 00:06:41,663
- My gosh. - Make way.

10
00:06:41,723 --> 00:06:43,463
- Goodness. - What on earth happened?

11
00:06:43,463 --> 00:06:46,023
- I have no idea. - I heard a gunshot.

12
00:06:46,023 --> 00:06:47,023
I heard the gun shot.

13
00:06:47,023 --> 00:06:48,523
- That is scary. - That is scary.

14
00:06:48,623 --> 00:06:49,623
Is that right?

15
00:06:50,063 --> 00:06:51,893
Goodness.

16
00:06:56,323 --> 00:06:57,793
Thank you for your cooperation.

17
00:06:57,793 --> 00:07:00,763
I will call you again if something comes up. I'll get going then.

18
00:07:09,493 --> 00:07:11,223
Can we talk now?

19
00:07:12,823 --> 00:07:14,063
By the way,

20
00:07:14,823 --> 00:07:17,763
I feel a little dizzy right now.

21
00:07:17,963 --> 00:07:19,223
Can we go inside and...

22
00:07:19,223 --> 00:07:20,763
Can't you grasp the situation?

23
00:07:21,423 --> 00:07:25,793
After checking if you are the stalker's accomplice or not,

24
00:07:25,793 --> 00:07:27,923
I'm going to decide whether or not to hand you over to the police.

25
00:07:27,923 --> 00:07:30,263
- I... - So why would I let you inside?

26
00:07:30,563 --> 00:07:32,893
I am not his accomplice.

27
00:07:32,893 --> 00:07:34,693
I was just trying to help you.

28
00:07:34,693 --> 00:07:36,393
So answer me.

29
00:07:38,293 --> 00:07:39,863
How did you get in a while ago?

30
00:07:42,323 --> 00:07:45,293
The gate and the front door were open.

31
00:07:45,993 --> 00:07:47,893
I think the stalker...

32
00:07:48,263 --> 00:07:49,763
left them open.

33
00:07:51,163 --> 00:07:55,323
The police can check that, so let's pass that.

34
00:07:55,323 --> 00:07:56,963
How did you know and come back?

35
00:07:57,363 --> 00:08:00,163
How did you know I was in danger and come back?

36
00:08:00,793 --> 00:08:01,893
That's because...

37
00:08:03,123 --> 00:08:05,723
the dog suddenly barked, so I followed him.

38
00:08:05,723 --> 00:08:07,423
You're saying it was because the dog barked.

39
00:08:08,293 --> 00:08:11,123
Yes. By the way...

40
00:08:14,323 --> 00:08:17,463
I... I feel...

41
00:08:19,723 --> 00:08:21,193
I feel a little dizzy right now.

42
00:08:27,463 --> 00:08:31,023
Hey! Wake up! Hey!

43
00:09:13,223 --> 00:09:14,263
No!

44
00:09:19,963 --> 00:09:20,963
What?

45
00:09:32,593 --> 00:09:35,833
Oh, my gosh!

46
00:09:45,363 --> 00:09:46,423
Yes.

47
00:09:46,493 --> 00:09:49,493
Where are you? Why are you still not home?

48
00:09:49,693 --> 00:09:51,893
You're supposed to type for me today.

49
00:09:53,623 --> 00:09:54,963
Is it because I'm not paying you enough?

50
00:09:54,963 --> 00:09:57,363
I am sorry, but I can't talk right now.

51
00:09:59,693 --> 00:10:01,833
Why do you sound so secretive?

52
00:10:02,593 --> 00:10:03,593
Where are you right now?

53
00:10:03,863 --> 00:10:05,793
I am in the bedroom of Writer Han Se Ju.

54
00:10:05,793 --> 00:10:07,223
What?

55
00:10:07,763 --> 00:10:09,523
Why are you there?

56
00:10:09,523 --> 00:10:11,863
I don't know. I lost my memory. I have to go. Bye.

57
00:10:15,563 --> 00:10:16,563
No way.

58
00:10:17,863 --> 00:10:19,863
I guess when you desperately yearn for something,

59
00:10:20,623 --> 00:10:22,423
you will have it in the end.

60
00:10:24,993 --> 00:10:26,063
Is nobody here?

61
00:10:29,863 --> 00:10:31,293
Look at these books.

62
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:36,063
Where is the front door?

63
00:11:15,293 --> 00:11:16,563
This place is so great.

64
00:11:18,963 --> 00:11:19,993
Look at the books.

65
00:12:44,493 --> 00:12:45,693
What are you doing here?

66
00:12:51,163 --> 00:12:52,163
Get out.

67
00:12:54,793 --> 00:12:55,863
Gosh.

68
00:12:56,493 --> 00:12:57,963
Wait, Mr. Han.

69
00:12:58,423 --> 00:12:59,563
Wait.

70
00:13:00,593 --> 00:13:02,923
Why do you keep entering my writing room without my consent?

71
00:13:03,423 --> 00:13:05,223
I am sorry. The door just opened.

72
00:13:05,963 --> 00:13:07,123
Goodness.

73
00:13:08,463 --> 00:13:09,463
It's nothing.

74
00:13:09,893 --> 00:13:11,723
Who are you really?

75
00:13:11,723 --> 00:13:13,493
Are you an elevator girl?

76
00:13:13,493 --> 00:13:15,723
Why does the door open every time you appear?

77
00:13:15,993 --> 00:13:17,693
Do you believe that now?

78
00:13:17,693 --> 00:13:18,793
What if I believe it?

79
00:13:18,793 --> 00:13:22,493
Will you just enter it without bothering to plan strategies?

80
00:13:22,663 --> 00:13:26,023
Why? Did you split up with that dog?

81
00:13:26,123 --> 00:13:28,493
Did he quit because the pay is too low?

82
00:13:29,923 --> 00:13:32,293
So you still don't believe what I said about the dog.

83
00:13:33,523 --> 00:13:35,263
Why are you interested in that typewriter?

84
00:13:35,423 --> 00:13:37,993
Are you checking if the candid camera is well?

85
00:13:38,123 --> 00:13:40,593
What are you... When did I... How could I...

86
00:13:40,593 --> 00:13:43,223
You brought it, so it's not impossible.

87
00:13:43,223 --> 00:13:44,763
When did I...

88
00:13:46,193 --> 00:13:48,423
A parcel is delivered to you. Wait!

89
00:13:48,423 --> 00:13:49,923
Is that parcel...

90
00:13:49,923 --> 00:13:50,923
Never mind.

91
00:13:51,323 --> 00:13:52,723
You pretended like you were never going to...

92
00:13:52,723 --> 00:13:54,163
wake up for a million years.

93
00:13:54,793 --> 00:13:55,893
Why did you come down?

94
00:14:19,023 --> 00:14:20,723
Just focus on the ramyeon.

95
00:14:24,323 --> 00:14:25,663
Have it quietly.

96
00:14:27,663 --> 00:14:29,693
If you can't ruminate like a cow,

97
00:14:29,693 --> 00:14:30,993
you should chew your food.

98
00:14:30,993 --> 00:14:32,593
I can't call the doctor twice.

99
00:14:33,123 --> 00:14:34,123
Okay.

100
00:14:35,323 --> 00:14:37,763
By the way, are you here because you don't want me to eat alone?

101
00:14:37,763 --> 00:14:38,893
Stop dreaming.

102
00:14:39,163 --> 00:14:40,763
I am watching you because I am afraid of...

103
00:14:40,763 --> 00:14:42,623
where you will go and what you will do.

104
00:14:43,263 --> 00:14:44,293
I see.

105
00:14:45,623 --> 00:14:47,123
Then do you believe that I'm not a stalker...

106
00:14:47,123 --> 00:14:48,423
Don't expect it.

107
00:14:49,093 --> 00:14:51,593
I'm still suspecting you.

108
00:14:53,093 --> 00:14:55,823
But I even saved your life. You are very cold-hearted.

109
00:14:57,693 --> 00:14:59,193
Let's straighten things out.

110
00:14:59,763 --> 00:15:03,223
I didn't even ask for help, and you jumped in.

111
00:15:04,123 --> 00:15:05,463
Like I said,

112
00:15:05,723 --> 00:15:07,093
I am a martial artist.

113
00:15:07,923 --> 00:15:09,763
I could've taken him down alone.

114
00:15:14,293 --> 00:15:16,493
But didn't you put me here instead of a hospital because...

115
00:15:16,493 --> 00:15:18,493
you were slightly worried and slightly thankful...

116
00:15:18,493 --> 00:15:20,923
There were reporters everywhere.

117
00:15:20,923 --> 00:15:22,593
The society and culture section of every newspaper will be filled...

118
00:15:22,593 --> 00:15:23,923
with articles about me by tomorrow.

119
00:15:24,523 --> 00:15:26,823
Do I have to take over the gossip section too?

120
00:15:27,163 --> 00:15:29,493
You are tenser than the Military Demarcation Line.

121
00:15:29,523 --> 00:15:31,223
There's no demilitarized zone.

122
00:15:34,723 --> 00:15:37,593
Have you learned shooting?

123
00:15:38,993 --> 00:15:41,063
You handled the gun very skilfully.

124
00:15:47,793 --> 00:15:48,893
Have you never learned it?

125
00:15:53,893 --> 00:15:55,493
I learned it a very, very long time ago.

126
00:15:58,893 --> 00:16:00,963
What do you mean by a very, very long time ago?

127
00:16:01,793 --> 00:16:02,863
When is that?

128
00:16:05,893 --> 00:16:07,023
When I was in high school.

129
00:16:07,323 --> 00:16:09,323
I was a member of a national shooting team.

130
00:16:09,523 --> 00:16:10,893
I quit in my 11th year.

131
00:16:11,723 --> 00:16:12,893
In high school.

132
00:16:15,793 --> 00:16:17,593
Are you developing a little bit of...

133
00:16:17,593 --> 00:16:18,863
- interest in me... - Give up your hope.

134
00:16:19,293 --> 00:16:21,593
I am not interested in other people.

135
00:16:22,463 --> 00:16:25,863
Why do you keep telling me to abandon things? Am I a monk?

136
00:16:29,963 --> 00:16:31,723
- Why did you quit? - Pardon me?

137
00:16:31,723 --> 00:16:33,863
Why did you quit shooting?

138
00:16:34,593 --> 00:16:35,893
Is it because of your trembling hand?

139
00:16:38,363 --> 00:16:39,663
It's a top secret.

140
00:16:39,763 --> 00:16:41,693
It's a sore spot for me.

141
00:16:41,693 --> 00:16:42,863
Are you an alcoholic?

142
00:16:42,863 --> 00:16:45,463
No. Everyone leaves me once they know my secret.

143
00:16:46,763 --> 00:16:49,163
I'll tell you about it when we become close.

144
00:16:52,393 --> 00:16:54,023
That's too bad.

145
00:16:54,523 --> 00:16:57,163
That means I'll never find out what it is.

146
00:17:01,223 --> 00:17:03,093
Go if you're done.

147
00:17:04,193 --> 00:17:05,693
I wish you much happiness.

148
00:17:12,033 --> 00:17:14,163
Shall I type it for you?

149
00:17:19,123 --> 00:17:20,263
Why?

150
00:17:21,033 --> 00:17:23,923
Did inhaling that bowl of ramyeon perk you up enough...

151
00:17:23,923 --> 00:17:25,723
to come up with a new ruse?

152
00:17:26,423 --> 00:17:29,493
It seems to be urgent, but you can't type well right now.

153
00:17:29,723 --> 00:17:33,463
I have a word processing certificate. I can type very fast.

154
00:17:33,463 --> 00:17:35,823
I can type from 700 to 900 keystrokes per minute.

155
00:17:36,223 --> 00:17:37,863
Can I do it for you and call it even?

156
00:17:42,323 --> 00:17:46,693
I can't believe I'm reading your rough draft. I'm so thrilled.

157
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:49,163
Don't say things like that.

158
00:17:49,163 --> 00:17:50,893
It creeps me out because it reminds me of "Misery".

159
00:17:50,893 --> 00:17:53,533
Oh, right. There's this line in "Misery".

160
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:56,793
"The only people who can read my manuscripts are my editor,"

161
00:17:56,793 --> 00:18:00,493
"my legal representative, and the one who saved my life."

162
00:18:01,293 --> 00:18:03,623
My gosh. Come to think of it, I did sort of save your life...

163
00:18:03,623 --> 00:18:05,063
I'm the one who saved your life.

164
00:18:05,293 --> 00:18:07,823
You passed out after breaking my golf club...

165
00:18:07,823 --> 00:18:10,723
which Tiger Woods gave me as a gift.

166
00:18:10,723 --> 00:18:14,763
Then I called my doctor who's expensive and saved your life.

167
00:18:15,033 --> 00:18:17,893
That is true, but I also saved your...

168
00:18:17,893 --> 00:18:21,463
Can you not breathe if you keep your mouth shut for a minute?

169
00:18:21,533 --> 00:18:23,093
Is it like a branchia?

170
00:18:24,093 --> 00:18:27,663
Do you want me to shut my mouth? I hope it's a misunderstanding.

171
00:18:28,723 --> 00:18:29,993
You understood me perfectly.

172
00:18:30,893 --> 00:18:31,893
Okay.

173
00:19:02,193 --> 00:19:03,193
My goodness.

174
00:20:57,463 --> 00:21:00,423
Go faster, will you? Speed up.

175
00:21:00,663 --> 00:21:02,823
You said yourself that you're a very fast learner.

176
00:21:02,823 --> 00:21:04,563
Will we ever finish it if you type like that?

177
00:21:04,563 --> 00:21:06,923
Then you should've paid more attention to your handwriting.

178
00:21:06,923 --> 00:21:11,293
That's obviously what's slowing me down.

179
00:21:12,893 --> 00:21:14,663
It's due in 30 minutes.

180
00:21:14,663 --> 00:21:17,293
It won't make it on the newspaper if the rotary press starts rolling.

181
00:21:17,293 --> 00:21:20,323
Did I tell you to get drunk and hurt your hand from a broken beer bottle?

182
00:21:20,323 --> 00:21:23,663
I never told you to act so recklessly just before the deadline.

183
00:21:59,823 --> 00:22:03,363
Go. The rotary press will start rolling in 10 minutes. Go!

184
00:22:04,023 --> 00:22:07,223
- Why should I? - You must be faster than me.

185
00:22:08,793 --> 00:22:11,823
Darn it. I'll give you half of my pay.

186
00:22:12,423 --> 00:22:14,193
Hurry up, please!

187
00:22:14,263 --> 00:22:15,293
Okay!

188
00:22:18,793 --> 00:22:19,823
Go.

189
00:22:26,223 --> 00:22:29,293
I told you to write something magnificent.

190
00:22:29,523 --> 00:22:33,763
Your novel is so third-rate. What a waste of newspaper space.

191
00:22:34,893 --> 00:22:36,723
Hey, Yoo Su Yeon!

192
00:23:14,393 --> 00:23:15,563
By any chance,

193
00:23:16,823 --> 00:23:19,663
did you just get a strange feeling too?

194
00:23:19,823 --> 00:23:22,563
Wait, you too?

195
00:23:24,893 --> 00:23:28,693
It felt as if time and space were collapsing.

196
00:23:29,823 --> 00:23:30,963
Isn't this...

197
00:23:32,523 --> 00:23:33,763
an earthquake?

198
00:23:34,023 --> 00:23:35,123
What?

199
00:23:39,993 --> 00:23:40,993
- It's an earthquake! - Earthquake!

200
00:23:45,970 --> 00:23:47,130
By any chance,

201
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:51,100
did you just get a strange feeling too?

202
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:54,000
Wait, you too?

203
00:23:56,400 --> 00:24:00,230
It felt as if time and space were collapsing.

204
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:02,330
Isn't this...

205
00:24:03,970 --> 00:24:05,270
an earthquake?

206
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,630
What?

207
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:12,600
- It's an earthquake! - Earthquake!

208
00:24:23,570 --> 00:24:26,830
I didn't know Seoul could be hit by such a strong earthquake.

209
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:29,570
There was no forecast or warning about this at all.

210
00:24:29,770 --> 00:24:32,830
Gosh, go away! Move away from me.

211
00:24:32,830 --> 00:24:35,800
I was here first. Why are you so selfish?

212
00:24:37,130 --> 00:24:38,800
Did you just snap at me?

213
00:24:39,230 --> 00:24:42,170
I guess nothing scares you now that you're faced with death!

214
00:24:43,130 --> 00:24:44,870
I am scared.

215
00:24:54,830 --> 00:24:55,900
Gosh.

216
00:25:02,530 --> 00:25:03,600
It stopped, right?

217
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:05,470
Yes, I think so.

218
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:35,430
Don't stare at me like that, please.

219
00:25:35,730 --> 00:25:38,070
It makes me think of "Misery". It's really creepy!

220
00:25:38,330 --> 00:25:39,400
Okay.

221
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:49,930
My gosh!

222
00:25:50,630 --> 00:25:53,400
Don't do that!

223
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:56,930
Okay.

224
00:26:05,470 --> 00:26:06,800
It's the moonlight.

225
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:44,800
You said we've met before, right?

226
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:48,170
When was it?

227
00:26:51,030 --> 00:26:54,100
Was it a very long time ago?

228
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:01,330
Well...

229
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:05,900
Well... It's...

230
00:27:07,270 --> 00:27:09,170
Se Ju!

231
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:10,470
Se Ju! Where are you?

232
00:27:13,230 --> 00:27:16,400
Why are all the lights off? Where is the switch?

233
00:27:22,370 --> 00:27:23,530
Are you okay?

234
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:29,030
Listen to me carefully.

235
00:27:29,170 --> 00:27:32,430
If he finds out what happened, it'll be complicated.

236
00:27:32,730 --> 00:27:36,170
So you should sneak out of the room.

237
00:27:36,670 --> 00:27:38,470
- Why should I? - Just listen to me.

238
00:27:38,830 --> 00:27:40,630
You'd better find a way to save yourself.

239
00:27:40,870 --> 00:27:44,600
When I'm back, you shouldn't be here anymore. Do you understand?

240
00:27:45,270 --> 00:27:49,030
Hang on a second. Mr. Han!

241
00:27:50,830 --> 00:27:54,600
What kind of mission is this in the middle of the romance?

242
00:27:55,800 --> 00:27:57,000
Se Ju!

243
00:27:58,170 --> 00:28:00,000
Se Ju! Are you all right?

244
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,330
Your arm!

245
00:28:02,470 --> 00:28:03,630
Did you get bitten?

246
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:06,700
As you can see, I'm fine. Stop overreacting.

247
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:10,200
Se Ju, I'm sorry I couldn't come earlier.

248
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:12,370
I'm just coming back from the business trip in Japan.

249
00:28:12,370 --> 00:28:14,100
Are you all right? Did you get hurt?

250
00:28:14,100 --> 00:28:17,770
You didn't have to hurry. It's dangerous because of the earthquake.

251
00:28:18,930 --> 00:28:20,400
Earthquake? What are you talking about?

252
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:25,700
My gosh, you're not fine at all.

253
00:28:25,700 --> 00:28:28,800
Is it post-traumatic stress disorder? Should I call the doctor?

254
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,700
My goodness, Se Ju.

255
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:41,100
Why does she have to interview me?

256
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:44,870
You said you saw and heard everything.

257
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:47,330
There's nothing more dangerous than the rumor.

258
00:28:47,370 --> 00:28:51,430
What if she says rubbish to look impressive?

259
00:28:51,430 --> 00:28:53,430
Don't you know those people exaggerate?

260
00:28:54,730 --> 00:28:57,830
So are you saying we should keep people's mouths shut with money...

261
00:28:57,830 --> 00:29:00,830
and publish an interview ourselves...

262
00:29:00,970 --> 00:29:02,700
before other journalists do?

263
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,900
You'd only write me a script to read off.

264
00:29:04,970 --> 00:29:06,930
There's no other way.

265
00:29:06,930 --> 00:29:10,370
What if the rumor runs that your novel encourages the criminals?

266
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:14,230
Not to mention the sales, your reputation would fall in an instant.

267
00:29:14,230 --> 00:29:16,700
Why is it because of my novel?

