00:46:24,530 --> 00:46:26,270
So you didn't do it.

536
00:46:29,530 --> 00:46:32,830
Okay. At least you are not using the dog as an excuse.

537
00:46:32,830 --> 00:46:34,570
You are not believing me right now.

538
00:46:35,430 --> 00:46:36,870
Did you just start talking to me as if I'm your friend?

539
00:46:36,870 --> 00:46:38,730
You talk like that. Why can't I?

540
00:46:38,770 --> 00:46:40,700
Why do you think I did it?

541
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:42,330
Let's hear the grounds for suspicion.

542
00:46:45,130 --> 00:46:49,300
Since you used the precise term "grounds", I will answer it.

543
00:46:49,530 --> 00:46:53,000
The only people who know about what we talked about that night...

544
00:46:53,330 --> 00:46:54,700
are the culprit, me,

545
00:46:55,700 --> 00:46:57,470
and you.

546
00:46:57,970 --> 00:47:01,230
Currently, the culprit is remaining silent about that night.

547
00:47:01,230 --> 00:47:03,730
So how do you think it leaked?

548
00:47:03,870 --> 00:47:06,530
Do you think I chattered about it like a mad man?

549
00:47:06,570 --> 00:47:07,570
So are you suspecting me again?

550
00:47:07,600 --> 00:47:09,030
You provided grounds for reasonable doubt.

551
00:47:09,030 --> 00:47:10,770
What should I do to make you believe me?

552
00:47:10,770 --> 00:47:12,670
Didn't I tell you?

553
00:47:14,030 --> 00:47:17,030
I don't believe people. Especially,

554
00:47:17,430 --> 00:47:20,000
not the ones like you, who put on an innocent face...

555
00:47:20,030 --> 00:47:21,700
and do wicked things at the back.

556
00:47:22,270 --> 00:47:25,530
If you won't believe me, why are you asking me this?

557
00:47:25,530 --> 00:47:28,970
If you admit your wrong deeds and ask for forgiveness,

558
00:47:29,430 --> 00:47:32,600
I will at least exonerate you.

559
00:47:33,230 --> 00:47:36,930
I will have to live longer to know when you will get it.

560
00:47:37,530 --> 00:47:39,570
Don't worry too much though.

561
00:47:39,830 --> 00:47:41,870
I won't make you take legal responsibility...

562
00:47:41,900 --> 00:47:43,100
for what happened that night.

563
00:47:43,500 --> 00:47:46,330
It was my mistake that I didn't make you shut your mouth.

564
00:47:46,330 --> 00:47:48,770
It was also my mistake that I let my guard down.

565
00:47:49,970 --> 00:47:50,970
But...

566
00:47:55,130 --> 00:47:57,030
I can't forgive you twice.

567
00:47:57,430 --> 00:47:58,500
Do you understand?

568
00:47:59,530 --> 00:48:01,170
I clearly warned you.

569
00:48:03,630 --> 00:48:05,100
Hey, Han Se Ju!

570
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:07,600
"Hey,"

571
00:48:08,330 --> 00:48:11,400
- "Han Se Ju"? - Why are you so high and mighty?

572
00:48:11,430 --> 00:48:13,530
I said I'm your fan, but you accused me of being a stalker.

573
00:48:13,530 --> 00:48:15,430
I saved your life, but you are ungrateful.

574
00:48:15,430 --> 00:48:17,730
Even if I do you a favor, you suspect me and tighten your guard.

575
00:48:17,730 --> 00:48:20,930
I told you. You didn't save my life. You were just being nosy.

576
00:48:20,930 --> 00:48:22,930
Do you think you are going to be successful forever?

577
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:25,170
I know for a fact that you'll also hit a dead end one day!

578
00:48:25,170 --> 00:48:27,500
There will come a time when you need someone's help!

579
00:48:27,500 --> 00:48:29,300
When that time comes, look around you.

580
00:48:29,530 --> 00:48:31,030
I'm sure nobody will be there for you.

581
00:48:32,500 --> 00:48:33,630
I am sorry.

582
00:48:34,770 --> 00:48:37,000
But I won't hit a dead end,

583
00:48:37,630 --> 00:48:40,300
and I will never create a situation where I'll need someone's help.

584
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:52,700
What are you doing?

585
00:48:52,700 --> 00:48:54,630
I shouldn't have saved you.

586
00:48:54,700 --> 00:48:57,030
If the same thing happens,

587
00:48:57,130 --> 00:48:59,970
then I will leave you to die. I will never help you!

588
00:49:00,930 --> 00:49:03,570
Darn it. It hurts.

589
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:18,100
He changed.

590
00:49:18,900 --> 00:49:22,800
He wasn't like that 10 years ago. He completely changed.

591
00:49:25,230 --> 00:49:26,770
It's over now.

592
00:49:28,530 --> 00:49:31,500
Bye, my beautiful days as a fan.

593
00:49:31,900 --> 00:49:33,830
I was a good fan.

594
00:49:34,030 --> 00:49:38,500
Seol will never be able to stop being a fan.

595
00:49:38,530 --> 00:49:40,970
Even if she accepts your love,

596
00:49:40,970 --> 00:49:43,530
her priority will always be Se Ju.

597
00:49:44,130 --> 00:49:48,530
On your lovely date night, she will call off the date...

598
00:49:48,530 --> 00:49:52,700
and run to Se Ju's signing event. That will always happen.

599
00:49:52,700 --> 00:49:55,830
That's the fate of a Han Se Ju fanatic's boyfriend.

600
00:49:56,330 --> 00:49:58,330
I can take that.

601
00:49:58,330 --> 00:50:02,200
I can allow one empty room in my lady's heart.

602
00:50:03,700 --> 00:50:06,630
Are you a pushover? And things have changed now.

603
00:50:06,630 --> 00:50:09,370
She's been watching him from a distance all these years.

604
00:50:12,970 --> 00:50:17,330
But now, she even went inside Se Ju's bedroom.

605
00:50:17,330 --> 00:50:19,330
- Bedroom? - Yes.

606
00:50:19,530 --> 00:50:22,000
I told you it was a guest bedroom.

607
00:50:22,400 --> 00:50:24,200
Will you keep spreading a false truth?

608
00:50:24,330 --> 00:50:27,170
What is up with the backpack? Are you going somewhere?

609
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:33,370
I am going to get some air.

610
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,970
My heart just broke.

611
00:50:37,230 --> 00:50:39,370
- What? Your heart broke. - What? Your heart broke.

612
00:50:39,500 --> 00:50:41,030
I realized that my idol...

613
00:50:41,230 --> 00:50:44,530
is just an idol.

614
00:50:44,530 --> 00:50:47,930
I decided to end my 10-year-long fan life.

615
00:50:50,230 --> 00:50:52,200
I'm going to become a normal person again.

616
00:50:52,830 --> 00:50:54,530
Excellent!

617
00:50:56,330 --> 00:50:59,800
I was going to ask you to take my script to Mr. Han...

618
00:50:59,830 --> 00:51:02,370
when you two become close.

619
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:04,500
Why do you stop being his fan?

620
00:51:04,970 --> 00:51:08,900
I prepared a love serenade for you. Listen.

621
00:51:21,270 --> 00:51:23,630
He's so simple.

622
00:51:45,870 --> 00:51:48,030
Thank you for your cooperation.

623
00:51:48,230 --> 00:51:52,230
We will monitor the conversation.

624
00:51:52,230 --> 00:51:55,130
So you don't have to worry about your safety.

625
00:51:55,130 --> 00:51:56,130
This way, please.

626
00:52:20,730 --> 00:52:22,430
You came here, Mr. Han.

627
00:52:24,870 --> 00:52:26,230
You must've been very surprised.

628
00:52:27,270 --> 00:52:29,570
My sister must've reported it to the media.

629
00:52:31,870 --> 00:52:32,970
Your sister.

630
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:36,970
I stopped her from doing it, but she must've felt bad for me.

631
00:52:37,630 --> 00:52:39,600
Are you still suspecting me?

632
00:52:39,600 --> 00:52:41,000
I didn't do it.

633
00:52:43,830 --> 00:52:45,530
The world must be in an uproar now...

634
00:52:45,530 --> 00:52:47,470
that they found out about our relationship.

635
00:52:48,730 --> 00:52:50,170
What do you mean by "our relationship"?

636
00:52:53,230 --> 00:52:54,970
What relationship are you talking about?

637
00:52:55,970 --> 00:52:57,530
Why are you pretending not to know?

638
00:52:57,700 --> 00:52:59,730
You gave me an inspiration to commit a murder,

639
00:52:59,730 --> 00:53:02,430
and I gave you an inspiration for your novel.

640
00:53:03,630 --> 00:53:04,800
Hey.

641
00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:09,030
I neither gave you an inspiration...

642
00:53:09,270 --> 00:53:11,000
nor received an inspiration.

643
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:14,530
A more educated word to describe it is "muse".

644
00:53:15,630 --> 00:53:17,600
I read it in your novel.

645
00:53:18,830 --> 00:53:22,800
Every writer wants a muse who can inspire him.

646
00:53:22,930 --> 00:53:25,770
So you are my muse,

647
00:53:25,800 --> 00:53:29,030
and I am your muse.

648
00:53:34,430 --> 00:53:36,470
I will make it clear.

649
00:53:40,270 --> 00:53:43,270
I've never read your letter.

650
00:53:43,530 --> 00:53:45,970
And my novel isn't about you.

651
00:53:45,970 --> 00:53:47,130
Don't worry.

652
00:53:47,530 --> 00:53:49,970
I will let you keep that story. That's what you want.

653
00:53:49,970 --> 00:53:51,000
Hey!

654
00:53:54,130 --> 00:53:56,030
I knew it the moment I saw you...

655
00:53:57,270 --> 00:53:59,230
that we are alike.

656
00:54:03,170 --> 00:54:04,970
Who are you really?

657
00:54:08,130 --> 00:54:10,600
I did a little research about you.

658
00:54:10,730 --> 00:54:12,200
I know almost everything about you.

659
00:54:15,230 --> 00:54:17,600
You were abandoned by your kin when you were little, right?

660
00:54:17,930 --> 00:54:20,030
Were you about 10 years old?

661
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:24,170
Your first guardian who was your relative took your parents'...

662
00:54:24,170 --> 00:54:26,530
death benefit and migrated without telling you.

663
00:54:27,070 --> 00:54:29,800
How many relatives did you have to stay with after that?

664
00:54:30,830 --> 00:54:33,300
By the say, why did you leave Writer Baek Do Ha's house?

665
00:54:33,900 --> 00:54:36,700
You stayed there for 5 long years since you were 16 years old.

666
00:54:37,500 --> 00:54:38,670
Were you...

667
00:54:40,070 --> 00:54:41,600
abandoned again?

668
00:54:45,770 --> 00:54:46,900
Shut your mouth.

669
00:54:50,430 --> 00:54:51,800
You are just like me.

670
00:54:53,130 --> 00:54:54,770
We were both abandoned.

671
00:54:55,030 --> 00:54:57,430
We are always worried about being abandoned again.

672
00:54:57,430 --> 00:54:59,370
We are scared, and we never trust other people.

673
00:55:00,330 --> 00:55:02,700
That's why I thought you would understand me.

674
00:55:02,700 --> 00:55:03,730
No.

675
00:55:06,700 --> 00:55:10,130
You are just a mad murderer and a stalker.

676
00:55:10,130 --> 00:55:12,900
But who made me the murderer? You made me commit a murder.

677
00:55:12,900 --> 00:55:14,000
No.

678
00:55:17,230 --> 00:55:21,230
You murdered simply because you wanted attention.

679
00:55:22,870 --> 00:55:25,530
You despaired of your low life.

680
00:55:25,800 --> 00:55:27,900
You must've committed a murder to vent your anger.

681
00:55:31,270 --> 00:55:32,370
Muse?

682
00:55:33,970 --> 00:55:35,070
Inspiration?

683
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:38,500
That's funny.

684
00:55:41,030 --> 00:55:42,930
I am nothing like you.

685
00:55:44,530 --> 00:55:45,700
You're different?

686
00:55:45,770 --> 00:55:48,130
Of course. I am.

687
00:55:48,700 --> 00:55:50,000
Stop...

688
00:55:50,930 --> 00:55:53,700
having a delusion that I'd understand you.

689
00:55:55,370 --> 00:55:57,270
Are you going to betray me?

690
00:55:58,570 --> 00:56:00,330
You deny me now...

691
00:56:00,870 --> 00:56:04,170
after you pretended to understand and click with me?

692
00:56:07,800 --> 00:56:11,700
If you are done talking, I'll get going.

693
00:56:13,070 --> 00:56:15,170
Because of you, my life came to an end.

694
00:56:15,670 --> 00:56:16,970
Your novel...

695
00:56:16,970 --> 00:56:20,070
and you writing have gotten me killed already.

696
00:56:20,070 --> 00:56:21,200
Grab him.

697
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:24,600
You should feel the same.

698
00:56:25,070 --> 00:56:28,400
Why don't you taste death with my writing.

699
00:56:56,970 --> 00:56:59,300
- Yes, sir. - Ms. Kang.

700
00:56:59,530 --> 00:57:03,000
Could you get me Jeon Seol's address?

701
00:57:18,870 --> 00:57:21,100
("Do Anything")

702
00:57:25,570 --> 00:57:27,170
Hello, it's Do Anything.

703
00:57:28,770 --> 00:57:30,730
Isn't this Jeon Seol's phone?

704
00:57:32,070 --> 00:57:33,230
Are you looking for Seol?

705
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:38,200
Who are you?

706
00:57:38,200 --> 00:57:41,400
Me? Wang Bang Wool fairy.

707
00:57:44,870 --> 00:57:48,130
So you have the special gift from...

708
00:57:49,530 --> 00:57:50,730
Why do you have that phone?

709
00:57:50,730 --> 00:57:53,000
Seol left and she's on temporary break for now.

710
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:55,800
She left the phone with me to manage the customers.

711
00:57:55,930 --> 00:57:58,370
What do you mean she left? Where did she go?

712
00:57:58,370 --> 00:58:00,570
She might have gone anywhere.

713
00:58:01,130 --> 00:58:04,000
She leaves whenever she feels confused.

714
00:58:05,500 --> 00:58:07,030
Thank you for letting me know.

715
00:58:10,030 --> 00:58:12,600
I can sense that you are in a very unstable state.

716
00:58:15,300 --> 00:58:18,430
Death, madness, delusion, anxiety,

717
00:58:18,430 --> 00:58:20,700
fear, resentment, and obsession.

718
00:58:21,400 --> 00:58:24,770
You have all the bad energy surrounding you.

719
00:58:24,870 --> 00:58:26,770
There might be a rumor too.

720
00:58:28,830 --> 00:58:31,430
Your life is very close with death.

721
00:58:32,370 --> 00:58:36,070
You'll have meet someone every time but you can't tell good from bad.

722
00:58:37,200 --> 00:58:41,300
Soon, you will have two special encounters.

723
00:58:42,530 --> 00:58:45,700
Try hard. You can only survive that way.

724
00:59:24,470 --> 00:59:25,730
You are just like me.

725
00:59:26,500 --> 00:59:27,930
We were both abandoned.

726
00:59:28,200 --> 00:59:32,170
We are always worried about being abandoned again.

727
01:00:10,600 --> 01:00:11,670
Hello.

728
01:00:11,770 --> 01:00:14,800
Mr. Han. From now on, don't watch TV or read any news on the Internet.

729
01:00:16,130 --> 01:00:18,900
Why? Something happened?

730
01:00:18,900 --> 01:00:21,700
Don't take calls from anyone but me. Wait. Just turn your phone off!

731
01:00:22,130 --> 01:00:23,930
Don't go outside for a while.

732
01:00:23,970 --> 01:00:25,530
What on earth is happening?

733
01:00:26,330 --> 01:00:27,370
It's breaking news.

734
01:00:27,400 --> 01:00:30,570
The imprisoned murderer who was responsible for shooting...

735
01:00:30,570 --> 01:00:32,730
committed suicide last night.

736
01:00:32,970 --> 01:00:37,430
In his prison cell, there were three pages of handwritten will.

737
01:00:37,470 --> 01:00:39,700
It was about his resentment...

738
01:00:39,700 --> 01:00:40,900
- towards Writer Han. - No way.

739
01:00:41,500 --> 01:00:43,070
No way.

740
01:00:46,670 --> 01:00:47,830
Oh, he's out.

741
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:49,070
He's out.

742
01:00:49,130 --> 01:00:51,770
Do you know anything about the culprit's suicide?

743
01:00:51,770 --> 01:00:53,930
Do you feel guilty or responsible for it in any kind of way?

744
01:00:53,970 --> 01:00:56,230
Did you really use the culprit for your own benefit?

745
01:00:56,270 --> 01:00:58,570
- Please let us know. - Please say something.

746
01:00:58,570 --> 01:01:01,570
- Tell us. - Please tell us.

747
01:01:03,030 --> 01:01:04,370
You should feel the same.

748
01:01:04,770 --> 01:01:08,130
Why don't you taste death with my writing.

749
01:01:08,600 --> 01:01:10,200
- What's the truth? - Please say something.

750
01:01:10,200 --> 01:01:12,930
- What happened? - Please tell us.

751
01:01:18,330 --> 01:01:20,930
(1 month later)

752
01:01:30,070 --> 01:01:31,130
Mr. Gal?

753
01:01:32,530 --> 01:01:34,430
Reporter Song, that jerk.

754
01:01:35,470 --> 01:01:36,800
Mr. Gal.

755
01:01:36,800 --> 01:01:38,830
Hey, Reporter Song!

756
01:01:41,430 --> 01:01:43,470
What brings you here?

757
01:01:43,470 --> 01:01:46,130
I came because I got worried.

758
01:01:47,100 --> 01:01:49,100
Words spread that Mr. Han disappeared...

759
01:01:49,100 --> 01:01:51,100
because he's experiencing a slump.

760
01:01:52,270 --> 01:01:53,370
What's going on?

761
01:01:53,570 --> 01:01:55,970
No, he didn't disappear.

762
01:01:56,400 --> 01:01:58,870
He's just spending time alone for creativity.

763
01:01:59,100 --> 01:02:01,370
He's busy because he's working on his next novel.

764
01:02:01,370 --> 01:02:03,670
He's just trying to focus on his work.

765
01:02:03,670 --> 01:02:05,830
Even we can't see him that often these days.

766
01:02:06,200 --> 01:02:07,570
Hello? This is Gal Ji Seok.

767
01:02:08,930 --> 01:02:10,000
Yes?

768
01:02:10,970 --> 01:02:12,100
Wait here. Yes.

769
01:02:12,870 --> 01:02:13,930
Okay. Wait.

770
01:02:17,170 --> 01:02:18,430
What happened?

771
01:02:29,770 --> 01:02:31,970
What did the doctor say?

772
01:02:37,430 --> 01:02:39,270
He said I have PTSD.

773
01:02:39,730 --> 01:02:41,300
It's a burnout syndrome.

774
01:02:41,530 --> 01:02:45,470
He said I can get better if I relax...

775
01:02:45,600 --> 01:02:47,030
and take proper rest.

776
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:48,630
He told me not to worry.

777
01:02:49,270 --> 01:02:50,430
Stand up.

778
01:02:52,570 --> 01:02:55,700
Telling someone not to worry when they're worried...

779
01:02:56,470 --> 01:02:59,830
is the same thing as telling an alcoholic to stop drinking.

780
01:03:00,130 --> 01:03:01,430
What a stupid doctor.

781
01:03:03,400 --> 01:03:05,700
Come on. Stand up.

782
01:03:06,430 --> 01:03:08,730
- What are you doing? - Come here.

783
01:03:11,570 --> 01:03:12,670
Come here.

784
01:03:15,730 --> 01:03:17,670
Sit down right now.

785
01:03:22,070 --> 01:03:25,600
Write. Stop acting so weak and start writing.

786
01:03:25,700 --> 01:03:27,500
"Writing is nothing."

787
01:03:27,600 --> 01:03:30,500
"I just sit in front of a typewriter and cough out some blood."

788
01:03:30,500 --> 01:03:32,170
That's what you said during your interview.

789
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:34,230
I just said what Hemingway said.

790
01:03:34,370 --> 01:03:37,130
"Don't try to make it perfect. Just write."

791
01:03:38,130 --> 01:03:39,330
That was by James Joyce.

792
01:03:39,370 --> 01:03:42,200
"You'll come up with ideas once you start writing."

793
01:03:42,370 --> 01:03:43,970
Stop it.

794
01:03:43,970 --> 01:03:46,800
"If you want water, you need to turn on the faucet."

795
01:03:46,800 --> 01:03:48,700
Stop it!

796
01:03:52,330 --> 01:03:56,000
If you're not going to write for me, shut that mouth of yours, you jerk.

797
01:04:01,570 --> 01:04:02,630
Are you being serious?

798
01:04:05,000 --> 01:04:06,170
What?

799
01:04:07,630 --> 01:04:09,300
Do you really need someone to write for you?

800
01:04:10,170 --> 01:04:11,330
What are you saying?

801
01:04:11,330 --> 01:04:13,730
It's been a month now. You're not sane.

802
01:04:13,730 --> 01:04:15,330
We need to come up with something.

803
01:04:15,330 --> 01:04:17,330
What are you saying right now?

804
01:04:17,330 --> 01:04:20,270
During the past month, you canceled on 2 magazines, 4 interviews,

805
01:04:20,270 --> 01:04:23,170
3 lectures, 2 TV shows, and 3 schedules abroad.

806
01:04:25,430 --> 01:04:27,270
Fine. Let's say I understand.

807
01:04:27,270 --> 01:04:31,030
You're human, so you could get tired and burn out once in a while.

808
01:04:32,700 --> 01:04:35,330
But we'll lose so much if the 10 million-dollar project goes wrong.

809
01:04:35,330 --> 01:04:37,400
Stop talking about that stupid project!

810
01:04:38,400 --> 01:04:40,730
Are you saying you're going to write for me or what?

811
01:04:40,730 --> 01:04:42,630
Just let me use your name!

812
01:04:45,130 --> 01:04:46,300
And what if I let you?

813
01:04:48,730 --> 01:04:50,430
Let's hire a ghost writer.

814
01:04:54,537 --> 01:04:55,977
Let's hire a ghost writer.

815
01:04:59,056 --> 01:05:00,086
What?

816
01:05:06,456 --> 01:05:07,586
You're kidding, right?

817
01:05:10,256 --> 01:05:11,386
Are you crazy?

818
01:05:11,386 --> 01:05:13,356
Only until you overcome the slump.

819
01:05:13,356 --> 01:05:15,216
No one would find it out.

820
01:05:15,216 --> 01:05:18,086
We are going to make a secret agreement with the ghost writer.

821
01:05:19,716 --> 01:05:20,786
Get out.

822
01:05:20,916 --> 01:05:23,556
Se Ju. You should keep a cool head.

823
01:05:23,556 --> 01:05:24,716
What we need is...

824
01:05:24,716 --> 01:05:26,416
not your work,

825
01:05:26,416 --> 01:05:28,386
but your name, which has the brand value.

826
01:05:28,386 --> 01:05:30,116
Stop it, you scum.

827
01:05:31,316 --> 01:05:34,116
I'm going to write. I will write.

828
01:05:35,816 --> 01:05:37,316
I'll make sure you get...

829
01:05:37,316 --> 01:05:40,086
the manuscript in your hand before the deadline.

830
01:05:40,886 --> 01:05:42,116
So get out.

831
01:06:12,216 --> 01:06:15,356
Hi, Mr. Yoo. How have you been?

832
01:06:16,316 --> 01:06:18,816
I'm fine as usual.

833
01:06:19,956 --> 01:06:23,586
Do you still ghostwrite biographies?

834
01:06:30,716 --> 01:06:34,686
Did you give up on becoming a writer?

835
01:06:51,256 --> 01:06:53,786
(It smells like...)

836
01:07:42,416 --> 01:07:44,056
Hey, what's up, man?

837
01:07:44,956 --> 01:07:46,856
Hi, Mr. Yoo. Have a seat.

838
01:07:51,626 --> 01:07:55,556
Mr. Yoo. You must not tell anyone...

839
01:07:56,686 --> 01:07:58,316
about the things I say from now on.

840
01:08:37,186 --> 01:08:38,286
(Carpe Diem)

841
01:08:50,086 --> 01:08:51,256
Hey.

842
01:08:52,556 --> 01:08:53,586
Hi.

843
01:08:56,016 --> 01:08:59,156
That girl is quite a good dancer, isn't she?

844
01:09:08,656 --> 01:09:09,716
It's a random dance.

845
01:09:14,316 --> 01:09:16,586
- We should dance as well. - The deadline is coming soon.

846
01:09:16,786 --> 01:09:20,086
I promised I'd send the manuscript for the newspaper by tomorrow.

847
01:09:20,416 --> 01:09:22,686
Deadlines are supposed to be missed.

848
01:09:22,986 --> 01:09:25,156
"Carpe diem". You should focus on the present.

849
01:09:25,156 --> 01:09:28,516
Love yourself as you are.

850
01:09:28,986 --> 01:09:30,126
Stop it.

851
01:09:30,386 --> 01:09:32,386
Come on.

852
01:10:35,356 --> 01:10:36,416
Hello.

853
01:10:36,956 --> 01:10:38,686
Is your manuscript ready?

854
01:10:38,686 --> 01:10:40,956
I still have some time until the deadline.

855
01:10:40,956 --> 01:10:45,086
Do you think you can make it until the deadline?

856
01:10:45,416 --> 01:10:47,256
Do you want me to make it or not?

857
01:10:50,686 --> 01:10:52,486
Mr. Han.

858
01:10:54,516 --> 01:10:57,086
About the ghost writer I talked about,

859
01:10:59,356 --> 01:11:02,626
I know a person who is perfect for it.

860
01:11:04,186 --> 01:11:06,286
If it's too stressful,

861
01:11:06,786 --> 01:11:09,626
you can still ask him to...

862
01:11:09,626 --> 01:11:12,016
It's almost done. Stop wasting my time. I'll hang up.

863
01:11:53,756 --> 01:11:55,916
We sing

864
01:11:55,916 --> 01:11:58,156
- The song of the glory - The song of the glory

865
01:11:58,156 --> 01:12:01,856
- Let's sing together - Let's sing together

866
01:12:01,956 --> 01:12:06,256
- My dream is whispering - My dream is whispering

867
01:12:06,286 --> 01:12:09,556
- The eyes are blazing - The eyes are blazing

868
01:12:10,016 --> 01:12:14,056
- Let's sing - Let's sing

869
01:12:14,056 --> 01:12:17,956
- People on the street - People on the street

870
01:12:18,126 --> 01:12:22,126
Let's whistle

871
01:12:22,216 --> 01:12:25,516
- For the youth of tomorrow - For the youth of tomorrow

872
01:12:25,986 --> 01:12:27,356
Is it because of the drink?

873
01:12:28,386 --> 01:12:30,356
Maybe it's the tranquillizer.

874
01:12:31,626 --> 01:12:32,626
Or maybe not.

875
01:12:33,286 --> 01:12:36,186
Is it a scene of a novel I was thinking of?

876
01:13:51,016 --> 01:13:53,516
Since when have I had such an antique item?

877
01:14:06,986 --> 01:14:08,356
(Carpe Diem)

878
01:14:26,626 --> 01:14:29,056
What's going on? Am I crazy?

879
01:14:29,556 --> 01:14:30,886
Am I getting crazy?

880
01:14:32,316 --> 01:14:34,186
Or am I already crazy?

881
01:14:36,356 --> 01:14:39,216
It'd be a big loss if we cancel this project.

882
01:14:39,886 --> 01:14:40,956
I should die.

883
01:14:41,626 --> 01:14:46,126
A writer who can't write is dead anyway.

884
01:14:49,416 --> 01:14:50,416
Well,

885
01:14:51,086 --> 01:14:52,486
why do I have to die?

886
01:14:52,516 --> 01:14:54,356
Think about all the things I've been through to get here.

887
01:14:56,256 --> 01:14:57,886
I can't fall like this.

888
01:14:58,216 --> 01:14:59,816
I cannot die like this.

889
01:15:00,086 --> 01:15:02,156
Darn it. Giving something and taking it away is...

890
01:15:02,186 --> 01:15:03,356
the worst thing one can do!

891
01:15:22,886 --> 01:15:25,586
Wait, just a second!

892
01:15:26,126 --> 01:15:28,716
I haven't even decided whether I want to die or not!

893
01:17:16,416 --> 01:17:19,816
Help... Help...

894
01:18:35,186 --> 01:18:37,386
If you ever end up in the same situation,

895
01:18:37,556 --> 01:18:40,486
I'll just let you die. I won't help you!

896
01:18:46,126 --> 01:18:47,126
Hey.

897
01:19:21,556 --> 01:19:24,126
(Chicago Typewriter)

898
01:19:24,386 --> 01:19:25,516
Any word from Se Ju?

899
01:19:25,516 --> 01:19:26,816
We can't get a hold of him.

900
01:19:26,816 --> 01:19:30,816
Han Se Ju, can you not come back? Or do you not want to return?

901
01:19:30,816 --> 01:19:32,216
Why am I here...

902
01:19:32,626 --> 01:19:33,816
It's Mr. Han's manuscript!

903
01:19:33,816 --> 01:19:34,986
He used a typewriter.

904
01:19:34,986 --> 01:19:36,986
We're getting publication rights inquiries from all over the world.

905
01:19:37,016 --> 01:19:38,716
Did I really write this?

906
01:19:38,716 --> 01:19:40,886
It is the story I wanted to write.

907
01:19:40,886 --> 01:19:42,516
You made a big contribution to your homeland.

908
01:19:42,516 --> 01:19:45,086
Isn't it a perfect revival? Do you think someone else wrote it?

909
01:19:45,086 --> 01:19:48,016
I'll turn Baek Tae Min into the second Han Se Ju.

910
01:19:48,556 --> 01:19:50,186
It's like a minefield.

911
01:19:50,816 --> 01:19:53,086
Who is it? I'm asking who it is. Answer me.

912
01:19:53,086 --> 01:19:54,416
I wrote it.

913
01:19:55,456 --> 01:19:57,626
I'm certain that I wrote it.
